# Unit 11

## 1. Reflection

This assignment strengthened my ability to apply quantitive risk modelling by using likelihood and impact to prioritise risks. I developed a better understanding of how to justify assumptions using academic and industry sources - particularly in the absence of organisational data. A key insight was recognising the limitations of simplified models especially the assumption that risks operate independently when in reality cybersecurity and supply chain risks are interconnected. This highlighted the importance of critical evaluation in risk modelling. Overall, the task improved my ability to support risk based decision making with structured, evidence based analysis while remaining aware of model limitations. 
